Restrictions of using APIs 
.private APIs - internal use only 
.partner APIs - shared with specific partners under agreement 
.public - found in the market for own use when there's no own specific API access from some entity that owns private APIs 


Disads 
.high cost - developing and maintaining them requires expertise 
.security risk - exposed endpoints can be vulnerable to attacks 
.versioning challenges - managign updates without breaking compatibility 
.dependency risk - relying on third-party APIs introduces failure points 

